WEBVTT

00:01.068 --> 00:09.274
♪♪

00:09.343 --> 00:11.576
[stressful whimper]

00:11.645 --> 00:15.113
♪♪

00:15.182 --> 00:16.715
Oh, no I have to...

00:25.192 --> 00:26.825
I can't believe the winter
to spring transition

00:26.894 --> 00:28.660
is almost here.

00:28.729 --> 00:32.564
La. La. La. laaaa. Oh, I
know. I love it so much,

00:32.633 --> 00:35.266
I gave it its own
term: Springsition!

00:35.335 --> 00:36.734
Ha ha ha ha !

00:36.803 --> 00:39.871
Oooh. I like that.

00:39.940 --> 00:42.307
I'm going to have to
re-label all my binders.

00:42.376 --> 00:43.642
Right after we finish--

00:44.878 --> 00:49.380
--Everything! We still
have so much to do!

00:49.449 --> 00:52.517
Oh, my bustles and
bows! Rarity, did we--

00:52.586 --> 00:55.353
Already hemmed, ruched
and cuffed, my dear.

00:55.422 --> 00:56.754
[relieved sigh]

00:56.823 --> 00:57.756
Oh!

00:59.126 --> 01:03.661
Rarity, no reason to panic,
but um, we seem to be

01:03.730 --> 01:06.264
temporarily low. And when
I say "temporarily low",

01:06.333 --> 01:07.899
I mean completely out of--

01:07.968 --> 01:11.302
--The baby blue sapphires?
They arrived this morning.

01:11.371 --> 01:13.238
Oh! Wonderful!

01:14.741 --> 01:16.074
[sigh of relief]

01:16.142 --> 01:17.709
[panicking again] Oh! What
about the design for the--

01:17.778 --> 01:18.843
--And done.

01:18.912 --> 01:21.579
Wow. You are good.

01:21.648 --> 01:24.916
And you've really outdone
yourself this time!

01:24.985 --> 01:29.220
The Morning Sunshine
Tulip frock is gorgeous.

01:29.289 --> 01:32.757
Oh, thank you. Now, I know
you're worried about something

01:32.826 --> 01:34.559
slipping between the cracks.

01:34.628 --> 01:39.230
but with your managerial skills
and my fabulous designs

01:39.299 --> 01:41.699
we have everything covered.

01:41.768 --> 01:45.870
You're right, you're right.
There are no cracks.

01:45.939 --> 01:47.939
Would you be a dear and fetch
me some vermillion satin

01:48.008 --> 01:48.707
from the back?

01:48.775 --> 01:49.975
And I'll start on the

01:50.043 --> 01:52.510
Eternal Elegance Empire
silhouette evening gown.

01:52.579 --> 01:54.812
My most certain pleasure.

01:54.881 --> 01:58.216
♪♪

01:58.285 --> 02:02.487
Oh! I love this picture!

02:02.556 --> 02:05.490
When was the last time we had
that kind of fun together?

02:05.559 --> 02:09.727
I... I can't remember.
Has it been that long?

02:09.796 --> 02:11.729
I guess I've been so
busy running my shop.

02:11.798 --> 02:15.366
Oh, no. Something, or
should I say somepony

02:15.435 --> 02:16.467
is slipping between
the cracks!

02:16.536 --> 02:18.736
[squeals of dismay]

02:18.805 --> 02:21.539
I miss my Sweetie Belle!

02:21.608 --> 02:22.774
[sobs]

02:22.843 --> 02:25.410
Rarity, we're running
low on vermillion satin.

02:26.847 --> 02:30.215
[blubbering]

02:30.284 --> 02:32.851
I... I can order more!

02:36.723 --> 02:39.991
<i>♪ My little pony,</i>
<i>my little pony ♪</i>

02:40.060 --> 02:41.960
<i>♪ Aaaahhh ♪</i>

02:42.029 --> 02:44.696
<i>♪ My little Pony ♪</i>

02:44.765 --> 02:46.598
<i>♪ I used to wonder what</i>
<i>friendship could be. ♪</i>

02:46.667 --> 02:48.367
<i>♪ My Little Pony ♪</i>

02:48.435 --> 02:51.436
<i>♪ Until you all shared</i>
<i>its magic with me. ♪</i>

02:51.505 --> 02:53.238
<i>♪ Big adventure! ♪</i>
<i>♪ Tons of fun ♪</i>

02:53.307 --> 02:55.073
<i>♪ A beautiful heart! ♪ ♪</i>
<i>Faithful and strong! ♪</i>

02:55.142 --> 02:57.576
<i>♪ Sharing kindness ♪</i>
<i>♪ it's an easy feat ♪</i>

02:57.645 --> 02:58.710
<i>♪ And magic makes it</i>
<i>all complete! ♪</i>

02:58.779 --> 03:01.379
<i>♪ To have my little pony ♪</i>

03:01.448 --> 03:04.682
<i>♪ Do you know you're all</i>
<i>my very best friends? ♪</i>

03:04.751 --> 03:07.252
♪♪

03:11.992 --> 03:16.361
[sobbing]

03:16.430 --> 03:19.731
...and this is when we pretended
we were storybook princesses

03:19.800 --> 03:21.599
[sniff sniff]

03:21.668 --> 03:23.468
and here we pretended

03:23.537 --> 03:26.404
we were on a dangerous-
yet-stylish safari...

03:26.473 --> 03:28.539
[sobbing]

03:28.608 --> 03:32.777
So many wonderful memories!

03:32.846 --> 03:35.346
[blast]

03:35.415 --> 03:39.751
[blubbering]

03:39.820 --> 03:42.754
Not to put too fine a
point on it but ....

03:42.823 --> 03:47.558
[loud bawling]

03:47.627 --> 03:54.633
Sweetie Belle loves playing
dress up. I miss her so much!

03:55.502 --> 03:58.569
Then why don't
you go visit her?

03:58.638 --> 04:02.874
I wish I could, but between
running three stores

04:02.943 --> 04:06.511
and the springsition,
I couldn't possibly!

04:06.580 --> 04:08.680
But you've already
done almost all the work.

04:08.749 --> 04:10.948
I can handle the rest.

04:11.017 --> 04:12.116
But--

04:12.185 --> 04:15.386
Rarity, go! I have
everything well in hoof.

04:15.455 --> 04:17.723
[blubbering]

04:18.992 --> 04:20.358
Point taken.

04:20.427 --> 04:22.927
I am going to visit my sister!

04:22.996 --> 04:25.396
Way to immediately
turn that around!

04:25.465 --> 04:27.031
We can spend the
whole day together!

04:27.100 --> 04:29.467
And we can do all of
her favorite things!

04:29.536 --> 04:31.336
I'm sure she'd
love that!

04:31.405 --> 04:33.371
Oh, Sassy, thank you!

04:33.440 --> 04:35.707
Of course! Now
get out of here!

04:35.776 --> 04:37.809
I'm going! I'm going!

04:37.878 --> 04:40.912
Hang on, sis. I'm coming!

04:40.981 --> 04:43.715
[giggling]

04:47.754 --> 04:48.820
Excuse us!

04:48.889 --> 04:50.421
Coming through!

04:50.490 --> 04:52.457
Cutie Mark Crusaders
mid-mission, here!

05:00.434 --> 05:01.700
[screams]

05:02.536 --> 05:03.701
[crash]

05:03.770 --> 05:06.804
♪♪

05:06.873 --> 05:09.140
That was fun!
Let's do it again!

05:09.209 --> 05:11.542
Scoot, we've got
a job to do.

05:11.611 --> 05:12.810
Later?

05:12.879 --> 05:16.013
All right, Chip Cutter.
We've done our part.

05:16.082 --> 05:18.015
The rest is up to you.

05:18.084 --> 05:20.585
You really think I have
it in me to be a sculptor?

05:20.654 --> 05:21.753
Yup.

05:21.822 --> 05:23.355
But... why?

05:25.192 --> 05:27.425
Because you said you
weren't good at anything

05:27.494 --> 05:29.060
except getting in trouble
for making sculptures

05:29.129 --> 05:31.629
out of your lunch, right?

05:31.698 --> 05:35.466
Yeah. I can't help it.
When I look at my sandwich,

05:35.535 --> 05:39.170
it's like it's just asking
me to turn it into a dragon.

05:39.239 --> 05:42.774
Well, what is this slab asking
you to turn it into?

05:46.646 --> 05:49.414
Hmmmm. I see.

05:49.483 --> 05:51.182
♪♪

05:51.251 --> 05:53.485
[jackhammer sound]

05:55.121 --> 05:55.853
[thunk]

05:55.922 --> 05:57.989
[cracking]

05:58.058 --> 06:01.092
♪♪

06:01.161 --> 06:04.162
Apple Bloom: Wow!
That's incredible!

06:04.231 --> 06:05.997
It looks
just like us!

06:06.066 --> 06:08.032
We knew you had
it in you, Chip.

06:08.101 --> 06:11.102
This is way better than
sandwich sculpting!

06:11.171 --> 06:13.572
Chip, we're proud of you.

06:20.714 --> 06:22.814
I finally got my cutie mark!

06:22.883 --> 06:24.649
Woo-hoo! All right!

06:24.718 --> 06:25.550
Yes!

06:25.619 --> 06:26.585
Way to go!

06:31.825 --> 06:35.860
Not a bad way
to start a day.

06:35.929 --> 06:38.062
Not a bad way
at all.

06:38.131 --> 06:40.899
Helping ponies is just about
my favorite thing to do.

06:42.769 --> 06:45.136
Another satisfied client!

06:45.205 --> 06:46.638
Mm hm!

06:49.175 --> 06:50.908
So who's up next?

06:50.977 --> 06:52.577
Pretty sure it's Zipporwhill.

06:52.646 --> 06:54.612
She needs help reconnecting
with her cutie mark:

06:54.681 --> 06:55.980
three puppy paw prints.

06:56.049 --> 06:57.348
When is she swinging by?

06:57.417 --> 07:01.853
Well, I think she should be
arriving right about now.

07:04.057 --> 07:06.224
Wow, you are good!

07:06.293 --> 07:08.726
Come on in, Zipporwhill.

07:08.795 --> 07:11.963
OK, so what seems to
be the problem exactly?

07:12.032 --> 07:16.801
It's my puppy, Ripley.
We used to be so close.

07:16.870 --> 07:19.737
In fact, I got my cutie
mark the day I found him

07:19.806 --> 07:21.739
and took him home.

07:21.808 --> 07:25.877
But now, it's like he wants
nothing to do with me.

07:25.946 --> 07:29.113
Don't you worry; you've
come to the right place.

07:29.182 --> 07:32.517
The Cutie Mark Crusaders
are on the job.

07:32.586 --> 07:34.252
Trust us, before
you know it,

07:34.321 --> 07:37.788
you and your puppy will
be back to being besties!

07:37.857 --> 07:40.157
You have the CMC guarantee!

07:40.226 --> 07:41.258
No matter what it takes,

07:41.327 --> 07:44.228
we promise you'll have
our full attention.

07:44.297 --> 07:46.197
Guess who's here to
spend the whole day

07:46.266 --> 07:48.232
with her little sister?

07:48.301 --> 07:49.600
Rarity!

07:49.669 --> 07:50.635
Whoa!

07:57.644 --> 08:01.012
So sorry, dear! You're tiny.
I didn't even see you there!

08:01.081 --> 08:03.214
Tend to get carried
away with my entrances!

08:03.283 --> 08:05.016
<i>♪ Ta da! ♪</i>

08:05.085 --> 08:08.019
Rarity, what are
you doing here?

08:08.088 --> 08:11.722
I am here to spend
the day with you!

08:11.791 --> 08:13.991
I'm so excited, I could
practically faint.

08:14.060 --> 08:16.160
You don't happen to have a
fainting couch in here, do you?

08:16.229 --> 08:18.596
NO!

08:18.665 --> 08:21.599
Of course not!
It's a tree house.

08:21.668 --> 08:23.768
That would be
très gauche.

08:23.837 --> 08:28.773
Right, well, I sure am happy to
see you! And spending the day

08:28.842 --> 08:31.042
with you does sound like
a lot of fun, but...

08:32.912 --> 08:35.846
I'm kinda right in the middle
of something important.

08:35.915 --> 08:37.782
I have responsibilities and--

08:37.851 --> 08:38.984
Oh...

08:41.855 --> 08:45.222
Go on, Sweetie Belle.
We've got this covered.

08:45.291 --> 08:47.725
How often do you get to
spend time with your sister?

08:47.794 --> 08:50.194
Yeah, go have fun.

08:50.263 --> 08:53.130
You sure you two can
handle our client here?

08:53.199 --> 08:58.302
"Client?" Oh, that
is so adorable!

08:58.371 --> 09:00.839
Uh, thanks? I think?

09:03.677 --> 09:08.112
Oooh! You have mints to
offer your 'clients'!

09:08.181 --> 09:10.081
How 'professional'!

09:10.150 --> 09:12.683
[munching]

09:12.752 --> 09:15.319
Are you sure you
two got this?

09:15.388 --> 09:17.388
We have it handled.

09:17.457 --> 09:23.094
Oh, my! Look at this
wall of satisfied customers!

09:23.163 --> 09:26.864
You girls really
have come a long way.

09:26.933 --> 09:29.333
Well, all right then.

09:29.402 --> 09:32.703
But let me know if you need
me or run into any trouble!

09:32.772 --> 09:35.740
Come on, come on. You'll never
guess what I have planned!

09:44.718 --> 09:46.217
[squeal] So fun!

09:49.456 --> 09:51.422
What?

09:51.491 --> 09:55.259
It's just I know how much
you love these puppet shows!

09:55.328 --> 09:56.727
I did.

09:56.796 --> 10:00.665
Oh, it's just like old times!
You, me, greasy popcorn...

10:02.502 --> 10:04.703
... it's like no time
has passed at all!

10:10.076 --> 10:13.712
[grunting]

10:17.083 --> 10:19.016
Ooh! Ooh! It's
your favorite part!

10:19.085 --> 10:29.160
♪♪

10:29.162 --> 10:34.465
♪♪

10:34.534 --> 10:39.270
Banana peels are so
very, very slippery!

10:39.339 --> 10:42.206
It's funny because
it's true!

10:42.275 --> 10:43.474
[forced laugh]

10:43.543 --> 10:45.743
[groan]

10:45.812 --> 10:47.712
What's the matter, darling?

10:47.781 --> 10:51.749
I um, guess I just prefer black
box experimental theater.

10:51.818 --> 10:54.852
What? Since when?

10:54.921 --> 10:57.322
I don't know. It's no
big deal. This is great.

11:00.226 --> 11:01.326
[jingle]

11:04.397 --> 11:07.064
OK, we're here!

11:07.133 --> 11:08.733
<i>♪ Ta-da! ♪</i>

11:08.802 --> 11:09.934
[giggle]

11:13.873 --> 11:16.207
Aren't you excited to
be back here again?

11:16.276 --> 11:20.344
Do I know my baby sister,
or do I know my baby sister?

11:20.413 --> 11:25.149
Uh... yeah. Where
is "here," exactly?

11:25.218 --> 11:28.185
Oh! Stop being so silly.

11:28.254 --> 11:30.155
You know this is your
favorite ice cream shop!

11:32.525 --> 11:37.027
Oh, right. From when
I was a little filly.

11:37.096 --> 11:40.397
And I convinced the original
owner to come out of retirement

11:40.466 --> 11:42.967
to make you your all-time
favorite dessert!

11:43.036 --> 11:50.308
♪♪

11:52.879 --> 11:56.247
Huh. I remember it
being much bigger.

11:56.316 --> 12:00.151
Well, go ahead. I know
you're dying to dig in.

12:04.224 --> 12:07.057
Well?

12:07.126 --> 12:12.496
That was... uh...
one tasty bite.

12:12.565 --> 12:14.899
Still a little hungry though.

12:14.968 --> 12:16.867
We can get another sundae!

12:16.936 --> 12:19.303
Chocolate with rainbow
sprinkles perhaps?

12:19.372 --> 12:21.572
I was thinking something
more like a salad.

12:21.641 --> 12:26.010
A salad? When did
you get so practical?

12:26.079 --> 12:30.014
Oh, um. I guess another
scoop would be fine!

12:30.083 --> 12:32.183
One more filly clown
surprise, please!

12:35.588 --> 12:36.988
[groan]

12:39.959 --> 12:41.125
Hey, Ripley!

12:41.194 --> 12:42.860
Look at me, over here!

12:42.929 --> 12:53.004
♪♪

12:53.006 --> 13:00.110
♪♪

13:00.179 --> 13:02.980
I know you must
be bored, darling.

13:03.049 --> 13:05.517
This is a very long line for
one of Twisty Pop's balloons!

13:06.920 --> 13:09.119
[groan]

13:09.188 --> 13:11.589
But just be patient; we'll
get you your favorite

13:11.658 --> 13:14.191
balloon bouquet and
it'll all be worth it!

13:14.260 --> 13:22.499
♪♪

13:22.568 --> 13:27.472
Who's a good puppy? Who's a good
puppy? You're the good puppy!

13:31.611 --> 13:35.480
Now come on, puppy-wuppy.
Get the bally-wally.

13:38.618 --> 13:40.351
Come on, Ripley!
Like this!

13:44.390 --> 13:46.523
Good, Scootaloo! See?

13:46.592 --> 13:50.027
[barking]

13:50.096 --> 13:52.162
It's not working.

13:52.231 --> 13:54.932
Maybe if the ball
tasted better?

13:55.001 --> 13:56.401
I don't think
that's it, Scoot.

13:57.704 --> 14:00.304
Doesn't look like
it's going so well.

14:00.373 --> 14:04.108
I'm just gonna do a quick
check with the CMC's.

14:04.177 --> 14:09.980
Well, I guess duty calls
and you have that now.

14:10.049 --> 14:11.215
What?

14:11.284 --> 14:13.918
Nothing, nothing, go on.

14:13.987 --> 14:17.187
Hey Sweetie Belle, how's
your day with Rarity going?

14:17.256 --> 14:21.258
Well, it's not exactly great.

14:21.327 --> 14:22.660
What do you mean?

14:22.728 --> 14:26.064
I don't know, it's like Rarity
doesn't even know me anymore.

14:27.600 --> 14:29.667
I wish we could say our
day is going better--

14:29.736 --> 14:32.403
[barking]

14:32.472 --> 14:35.272
--but we can't.

14:35.341 --> 14:37.107
Seems like Zipporwhill's puppy

14:37.176 --> 14:38.977
doesn't want anything
to do with her!

14:45.151 --> 14:48.485
Hmmm. I see what you mean.

14:48.554 --> 14:51.655
Ya know, it's an
awfully big puppy.

14:51.724 --> 14:55.292
Sweetie Belle! Hurry;
he's making it!

14:55.361 --> 14:56.561
Gotta go.

15:03.436 --> 15:06.603
I know just what
to do with this!

15:06.672 --> 15:10.741
♪♪

15:10.810 --> 15:12.076
And pose!

15:14.247 --> 15:16.213
And pose!

15:16.282 --> 15:17.748
Love the camera!

15:17.817 --> 15:20.351
Hate the camera.

15:20.420 --> 15:21.486
Love it again!

15:25.725 --> 15:30.361
Sweetie Belle, you did "hate the
camera" for all these shots!

15:30.430 --> 15:32.363
Let's do it again.

15:32.432 --> 15:33.230
No!

15:33.299 --> 15:35.265
[gasp]

15:35.334 --> 15:37.534
C'mon Zipporwhill,
you can do this!

15:37.603 --> 15:48.579
♪♪

15:48.648 --> 15:50.647
What do you mean no?

15:50.716 --> 15:56.253
Rarity, this is hard for
me to say, but... um...

15:56.322 --> 15:58.455
Sweetie Belle, what is it?

15:58.524 --> 16:00.724
You've been acting
weird all day.

16:00.793 --> 16:03.394
You used to love doing
these things with me!

16:03.463 --> 16:08.665
That's just it! I used to!
That's not who I am anymore.

16:08.734 --> 16:12.636
This isn't who I am. My cutie
mark must be for something else

16:12.705 --> 16:16.040
because my puppy just
doesn't love me anymore!

16:20.113 --> 16:23.747
But it is you. You love
puppet shows and dressing up

16:23.816 --> 16:27.818
and taking silly photos and tiny
little clown-shaped ice creams!

16:27.887 --> 16:31.221
Really?! If you still think
I like doing this stuff,

16:31.290 --> 16:33.358
then maybe you don't
know me at all.

16:35.695 --> 16:38.296
[whimper]

16:42.201 --> 16:45.235
[sobbing]

16:45.304 --> 16:48.572
I can't believe Sweetie Belle
talked to me like that.

16:48.641 --> 16:50.808
And after everything I
did to set up a whole day of

16:50.877 --> 16:53.143
doing her favorite things!

16:53.212 --> 16:56.146
I mean, accusing me
of not knowing her!

16:56.215 --> 16:58.082
I know her better than anypony!

17:01.487 --> 17:04.822
Thank you, Twisty, but the
hard truth is my sister

17:04.891 --> 17:07.858
is being unappreciative
right now.

17:07.927 --> 17:10.395
And I'm going to go and give
her a piece of my mind!

17:16.802 --> 17:19.303
Hey, Zipporwhill. What
are you doing here?

17:19.372 --> 17:21.271
Where are Apple
Bloom and Scootaloo?

17:21.340 --> 17:23.373
They're with my puppy.

17:23.442 --> 17:27.578
He seems to like them
better than me anyway.

17:27.647 --> 17:30.481
Now I'm sure that's not true.

17:30.550 --> 17:34.852
It is. He doesn't like doing
anything with me anymore.

17:34.921 --> 17:37.454
[sigh]

17:37.523 --> 17:40.157
He didn't even want
to play with this.

17:40.226 --> 17:42.526
And all puppies love these.

17:42.595 --> 17:47.531
[sobbing]

17:47.600 --> 17:51.135
I think that might be your
problem right there. Come on!

17:51.204 --> 17:54.605
♪♪

17:58.611 --> 18:01.912
Find Zipporwhill, Ripley.

18:01.981 --> 18:04.582
Woof woof. Zipporwhill woof?

18:07.353 --> 18:08.919
It's hopeless.

18:08.988 --> 18:10.421
Sweetie Belle!

18:10.489 --> 18:15.292
Zipporwhill! We're sorry we
haven't figured this out yet.

18:15.361 --> 18:18.463
Don't worry, girls; I
think I cracked this one.

18:20.466 --> 18:25.269
There she is! Oh, dear.
Really should have changed.

18:25.338 --> 18:28.172
No matter. I'm going to give
her quite the talking to!

18:29.675 --> 18:32.376
Right after she's done
with her conversation.

18:32.445 --> 18:35.345
Anger is no excuse for
poor manners, after all.

18:35.414 --> 18:39.183
OK. Zipporwhill,
what do you see?

18:39.252 --> 18:40.817
My puppy?

18:40.886 --> 18:45.722
That's not what I see.
I see a full grown dog.

18:45.791 --> 18:48.759
He did get bigger, I guess.

18:48.828 --> 18:51.829
He's not just bigger,
he's older too.

18:54.600 --> 18:56.300
You don't still play
with the same toys

18:56.369 --> 18:59.303
from when you were
a foal, do you?

18:59.372 --> 19:05.876
Oh. Ohhh! This squeaker is
a little small for him now.

19:05.945 --> 19:08.845
It's just hard for me to
believe he's not the same

19:08.914 --> 19:11.782
adorable little guy
I found anymore.

19:11.851 --> 19:14.818
I understand. But doing
things like you used to

19:14.887 --> 19:17.354
won't turn him
back into a puppy.

19:17.423 --> 19:19.623
So what do I do?

19:19.692 --> 19:21.625
Treat him like the dog he is

19:21.694 --> 19:23.894
and find new favorite
things to do together.

19:23.963 --> 19:25.395
You think so?

19:25.464 --> 19:26.563
I know so!

19:26.632 --> 19:28.732
Rarity!?

19:28.801 --> 19:32.736
Oh, Sweetie Belle. I heard what
you said and you are so right.

19:32.805 --> 19:34.271
About the dog?

19:34.340 --> 19:37.441
Yes, but about us, too!

19:37.510 --> 19:40.944
The truth is, I know you're
not a little filly anymore.

19:41.013 --> 19:42.846
But it's just the
last time we did

19:42.915 --> 19:47.017
all of those things together,
I... I didn't realize

19:47.086 --> 19:52.322
it was going to be
the last, last time.

19:52.391 --> 19:54.691
I loved doing those
things with you;

19:54.760 --> 19:56.927
it's hard for me to
let that go.

19:56.996 --> 20:02.966
Aw, Rarity. I love being with
you too. That will never change!

20:03.035 --> 20:06.270
But maybe we could just try to
do different things together?

20:06.339 --> 20:16.380
♪♪

20:16.449 --> 20:19.917
What is it, puppy?
I mean, Ripley?

20:29.729 --> 20:31.762
I love you too, Ripley.

20:31.831 --> 20:34.965
♪♪

20:35.034 --> 20:37.434
Thank you, Crusaders!

20:37.503 --> 20:39.403
No problem!

20:39.472 --> 20:42.739
[laughter]

20:42.808 --> 20:45.509
Sweetie Belle, I
am so very proud

20:45.578 --> 20:47.911
of the pony
you've grown into.

20:47.980 --> 20:50.314
And I'm proud that
no matter what,

20:50.383 --> 20:53.350
I'll always be
your little sister.

20:53.419 --> 20:55.352
I uhh, have a little bit of time

20:55.421 --> 20:57.587
before I have to
head to Canterlot.

20:57.656 --> 21:00.424
Could we spend it together?

21:00.493 --> 21:03.727
What would a grown pony
like you want to do?

21:03.796 --> 21:07.431
Well, I do have one idea.

21:07.500 --> 21:14.104
♪♪

21:14.173 --> 21:17.541
I didn't realize your idea
would be such a delicious one.

21:17.610 --> 21:19.710
I don't know how I'm
going to finish this.

21:19.779 --> 21:21.445
Oh, I'll help you!
